org.kitesdk.data

Interface Syncable


  • public interface Syncable
    A writer that can guarantee data is persisted to disk.

    When sync() returns, data already written is flushed to data nodes responsible for replicas and persisted to disk, not just to the underlying OS buffer.

    Since:
    0.18.0

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void sync()
      Ensure that data has been synced to disk on all replica data nodes.
